# Config Changes Go in conf/import/

When changing any server configuration (battle, map, char, login, inter, web, client, etc.), put the override in the matching file under `conf/import/` instead of editing the base config files under `conf/`.

This keeps customizations separate from upstream defaults so they survive updates.

## Mapping

- `conf/battle/*.conf` overrides → `conf/import/battle_conf.txt`
- `conf/map_athena.conf` overrides → `conf/import/map_conf.txt`
- `conf/char_athena.conf` overrides → `conf/import/char_conf.txt`
- `conf/login_athena.conf` overrides → `conf/import/login_conf.txt`
- `conf/inter_athena.conf` overrides → `conf/import/inter_conf.txt`
- `conf/web_athena.conf` overrides → `conf/import/web_conf.txt`

## Rules

- Never edit base config files directly to change a value; add/override the key in the import file.
- Add a brief comment noting which base file the setting comes from.

## Example

To make players respawn with full HP/SP, add to `conf/import/battle_conf.txt`:

```
// conf/battle/player.conf
restart_hp_rate: 100
restart_sp_rate: 100
```
